into a theater for movie lovers.

477
00:35:54,719 --> 00:35:58,659
Mr. Kang's team is working on
a project related to theaters too.

478
00:35:59,030 --> 00:36:01,599
This is our chance
to prove ourselves.

479
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:04,730
Are we going to set the theme
ourselves as well?

480
00:36:05,429 --> 00:36:08,199
Do you think marketing
is all about...

481
00:36:08,269 --> 00:36:10,809
sitting at the desk
writing a few articles?

482
00:36:11,869 --> 00:36:14,840
You have to try the whole process...

483
00:36:14,880 --> 00:36:16,809
from planning to marketing
yourself...

484
00:36:17,079 --> 00:36:19,679
to get an idea of how PR works.

485
00:36:20,179 --> 00:36:23,920
Ro Woon, go check the place
with Boss.

486
00:36:23,949 --> 00:36:25,250
Can't I go?

487
00:36:27,659 --> 00:36:29,489
I think Ro Woon should go.

488
00:36:29,690 --> 00:36:31,130
Okay.

489
00:36:43,340 --> 00:36:45,409
Can't I know what's on your mind?

490
00:36:57,250 --> 00:36:59,389
You fell in love with someone
you shouldn't love, didn't you?

491
00:37:00,619 --> 00:37:03,630
She's your employee,
and she's another employee's girl.

492
00:37:14,739 --> 00:37:17,510
Do you see?
The red light means "stop".

493
00:37:17,570 --> 00:37:19,409
The yellow light means he's
available only for urgent matters.

494
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:22,380
- The green light is...
- Does the green light ever turn on?

495
00:37:22,710 --> 00:37:24,480
Gosh.

496
00:37:25,050 --> 00:37:28,019
I'll leave for the theater first.

497
00:37:29,449 --> 00:37:30,690
Let me go with you.

498
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:34,519
No. The red light is on.

499
00:37:34,559 --> 00:37:36,260
Sort out your thoughts.

500
00:37:36,690 --> 00:37:38,530
Come when the green light is on.

501
00:37:40,460 --> 00:37:41,530
Go.

502
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:43,869
Take your time.

503
00:37:44,429 --> 00:37:46,539
- Go.
- I'm going.

504
00:37:53,409 --> 00:37:54,610
A red light.

505
00:38:08,590 --> 00:38:10,690
I realized I should stop.

506
00:38:29,780 --> 00:38:31,210
Still, I...

507
00:38:32,579 --> 00:38:33,650
Gosh.

508
00:38:49,699 --> 00:38:53,369
Is the green light on yet?

509
00:39:39,719 --> 00:39:40,820
I'm sorry.

510
00:39:41,349 --> 00:39:42,619
Hey, Hwan Gi.

511
00:39:48,590 --> 00:39:51,190
Did you not see me?
Or are you just pretending?

512
00:39:51,730 --> 00:39:54,000
You were all I could see
even from across the street.

513
00:39:55,969 --> 00:39:57,000
Yun Jung.

514
00:39:57,570 --> 00:39:59,440
Every time I see you,
I feel like it's been so long.

515
00:40:06,179 --> 00:40:08,139
Please leave a message
after the tone.

516
00:40:08,179 --> 00:40:09,949
I'd appreciate it
if he at least picks up.

517
00:40:11,010 --> 00:40:13,380
Come to think of it, I've never
talked to him on the phone.

518
00:40:14,349 --> 00:40:16,849
Oh, that's right.

519
00:40:17,590 --> 00:40:19,219
He has telephone phobia.

520
00:40:40,710 --> 00:40:43,150
I actually saw you at the airport
a little while ago.

521
00:40:43,309 --> 00:40:45,110
That was you, wasn't it?

522
00:40:45,250 --> 00:40:48,780
Oh, the airport? Right.

523
00:40:49,389 --> 00:40:51,820
Even on that day, you walked away
as if you didn't see me.

524
00:40:53,719 --> 00:40:56,730
Right, you probably didn't have
the guts to face me...

525
00:40:56,829 --> 00:40:58,889
after standing me up
like that three years ago.

526
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:02,900
I've developed trauma
about Christmas.

527
00:41:06,070 --> 00:41:08,840
- I'm sorry. Back then, I was...
- Forget it.

528
00:41:10,010 --> 00:41:11,869
I actually wrote a ton
of mean comments...

529
00:41:11,909 --> 00:41:15,139
on the articles about your being an
abusive boss, so let's call it even.

530
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:21,880
No, that's actually not enough.

531
00:41:23,590 --> 00:41:25,250
How about you buy me
a cup of coffee?

532
00:41:25,550 --> 00:41:26,590
Coffee?

533
00:41:28,820 --> 00:41:31,889
I have to get going now, though.

534
00:42:08,030 --> 00:42:09,159
You're in trouble.

535
00:42:10,230 --> 00:42:12,000
You won't be able
to run away this time.

536
00:42:14,599 --> 00:42:15,909
And here's a cup of coffee.

537
00:42:17,239 --> 00:42:18,769
That's for someone else.

538
00:42:21,679 --> 00:42:23,980
I'm sorry. I already had a sip.

539
00:42:24,510 --> 00:42:26,349
I was going to give it to Ro Woon.

540
00:42:26,719 --> 00:42:29,179
- I'll visit you at work soon.
- What?

541
00:42:29,619 --> 00:42:31,719
I want to talk to you about doing
PR work for the new exhibition.

542
00:42:31,989 --> 00:42:35,820
You won't stand me up if I'm
meeting you as your client, right?

543
00:42:37,929 --> 00:42:39,130
About three years ago...

544
00:42:39,960 --> 00:42:42,230
I had a bit of a situation.

545
00:42:42,300 --> 00:42:45,730
I know. It was probably something
you couldn't tell me.

546
00:42:46,300 --> 00:42:49,409
Otherwise, you would've told me
the reason three years ago.

547
00:42:52,909 --> 00:42:54,710
But I'm serious about the work.

548
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:56,809
I was actually on the lookout
for a PR agency.

549
00:42:57,309 --> 00:42:58,480
Help me out.

550
00:42:59,079 --> 00:43:00,179
All right, then.

551
00:43:01,519 --> 00:43:04,190
I'm going to boss you around.
Brace yourself.

552
00:43:26,239 --> 00:43:28,239
Is it still the red light?

553
00:45:15,780 --> 00:45:17,650
I wanted to be
by her side like this...

554
00:45:18,349 --> 00:45:19,760
for just a little longer.

555
00:46:01,860 --> 00:46:06,000
Would it be okay for me to stay
by her side if I keep this distance?

556
00:46:09,539 --> 00:46:11,739
("Don't Forget Me")

557
00:46:19,719 --> 00:46:21,449
You didn't meet him at the theater?

558
00:46:24,989 --> 00:46:28,090
He said he was headed there
as he was leaving yesterday.

559
00:46:28,590 --> 00:46:30,690
Did something else pop up?

560
00:46:30,789 --> 00:46:32,860
I guess he met
another girl or something.

561
00:46:44,670 --> 00:46:48,010
He's been smirking too.
He seems to be in a good mood today.

562
00:46:51,849 --> 00:46:52,849
Then...

563
00:46:53,780 --> 00:46:55,849
is it the green light today, Boss?

564
00:46:57,190 --> 00:46:59,690
If that's the case, do you mind
taking a look at my proposal?

565
00:46:59,760 --> 00:47:01,190
To get on with the trend,

566
00:47:01,389 --> 00:47:04,489
I thought we could use "virtual
reality cinema" as our theme.

567
00:47:04,630 --> 00:47:06,599
Yes, I've read your proposal.

568
00:47:07,860 --> 00:47:08,900
But...

569
00:47:10,530 --> 00:47:13,340
It'd be different for games,
but there isn't enough content.

570
00:47:13,670 --> 00:47:15,000
The trend isn't there yet.

571
00:47:15,769 --> 00:47:16,940
He's right.

572
00:47:18,210 --> 00:47:20,539
Sun Bong,
you're being cynical again.

573
00:47:20,579 --> 00:47:21,639
Also,

574
00:47:22,280 --> 00:47:23,880
prolonged use of VR headsets...

575
00:47:23,980 --> 00:47:27,550
can induce motion sickness or
headaches. How will you tackle that?

576
00:47:27,579 --> 00:47:30,320
What will you do if people complain
about blurred vision or eye fatigue?

577
00:47:30,349 --> 00:47:33,090
Do you have a plan for how you will
deal with such problems?

578
00:47:34,289 --> 00:47:36,590
Those are issues
that we can't overlook.

579
00:47:37,059 --> 00:47:39,360
Sun Bong, do you have an idea then?

580
00:47:39,460 --> 00:47:42,199
Something unique that can appeal
to the target group.

581
00:47:43,630 --> 00:47:45,230
- No, I don't.
- See?

582
00:47:45,329 --> 00:47:46,469
What is wrong with you?

583
00:47:46,769 --> 00:47:49,400
You have no clue either.

584
00:47:49,570 --> 00:47:52,409
Boss, please let us know
what you think.

585
00:47:57,679 --> 00:47:59,579
I need some time to think.

586
00:47:59,679 --> 00:48:03,489
We need to act fast so that we can
become the first one in Korea.

587
00:48:03,789 --> 00:48:05,489
Yes, I know that. But...

588
00:48:11,329 --> 00:48:13,460
The best, the biggest,
and the first.

589
00:48:13,599 --> 00:48:15,730
I must say Korean people
can be so lame.

590
00:48:15,760 --> 00:48:18,070
The just love those superlatives.

591
00:48:18,170 --> 00:48:20,739
They think that's what
PR work is all about.

592
00:48:20,769 --> 00:48:21,969
How simple-minded.

593
00:48:22,969 --> 00:48:26,280
That was blunt, but he's not wrong.

594
00:48:27,039 --> 00:48:29,909
I'll take some time
to think about it.

595
00:48:37,449 --> 00:48:38,989
He loves taking time.

596
00:48:39,190 --> 00:48:41,360
I guess
the red light is on again today.

597
00:48:43,429 --> 00:48:45,289
About the signal lights...

598
00:48:45,730 --> 00:48:47,960
Don't you think the idea
is a bit too childish?

599
00:48:48,030 --> 00:48:50,630
A full-fledged adult is walking
around with colorful stickers.

600
00:48:50,730 --> 00:48:52,900
What is that seriously? Is he
a pervert or what? How embarrassing.

601
00:48:53,139 --> 00:48:56,369
Plus, he's our leader,

602
00:48:56,570 --> 00:48:59,739
yet he communicates with us
only when he wants to.

603
00:48:59,780 --> 00:49:01,579
What kind of nonsense is that?

604
00:49:02,610 --> 00:49:04,980
Stop ruining it.

605
00:49:05,380 --> 00:49:06,849
I was going to stop.

606
00:49:25,099 --> 00:49:26,199
Gyo Ri.

607
00:49:27,170 --> 00:49:28,769
Why are you dolling up?

608
00:49:28,869 --> 00:49:31,110
Do you have a date?
I'm sure you don't.

609
00:49:32,610 --> 00:49:34,380
- Why don't we go for...
- Gyo Ri.

610
00:49:34,909 --> 00:49:36,550
- Should we go on a date?
- Sorry?

611
00:49:37,380 --> 00:49:40,050
- Are you asking me?
- Yes.

612
00:49:40,679 --> 00:49:42,780
I'd like to treat you
to a nice dinner.

613
00:49:42,880 --> 00:49:45,349
You look especially pretty today.

614
00:49:49,889 --> 00:49:51,460
(VR Movies)

615
00:49:53,400 --> 00:49:54,760
That's so random.

616
00:49:55,199 --> 00:49:56,329
Just the two of you?

617
00:49:56,599 --> 00:49:58,900
Yes. I have something to tell her
in person.

618
00:49:59,500 --> 00:50:01,900
- Let's go, Gyo Ri.
- Okay.

619
00:50:02,869 --> 00:50:04,639
- Let's go.
- Okay.

620
00:50:05,269 --> 00:50:06,340
Let's go.

621
00:50:08,440 --> 00:50:09,639
Let's go.

622
00:50:10,610 --> 00:50:11,880
What do you want to eat?

623
00:50:12,280 --> 00:50:14,719
Anything is fine.

624
00:50:14,849 --> 00:50:16,119
What about steaks?

625
00:50:19,920 --> 00:50:23,389
Yoo Hee, why don't we have
some spicy food and soju?

626
00:50:23,590 --> 00:50:25,260
I need to go home and feed my kids.

627
00:50:25,960 --> 00:50:29,099
Your sons will leave you
for other girls after all.

628
00:50:29,130 --> 00:50:30,400
Live your life.

629
00:50:30,429 --> 00:50:34,000
Stop observing
and laughing at others.

630
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:37,170
Live your life, okay?

631
00:50:47,579 --> 00:50:51,389
My goodness. Do you still have
hope for the VR cinema?

632
00:50:51,889 --> 00:50:54,119
I can give you some advice
if you buy me dinner.

633
00:50:54,320 --> 00:50:55,420
I'm okay.

634
00:50:55,719 --> 00:51:00,199
I have to do some more research
on VR theaters.

635
00:51:01,230 --> 00:51:02,900
I'll get going.

636
00:51:03,769 --> 00:51:05,099
- Wait.
- Sorry.

637
00:51:05,400 --> 00:51:06,769
I'm leaving.

638
00:51:11,039 --> 00:51:13,539
Why does it feel like
there's someone behind me?

639
00:51:31,929 --> 00:51:34,159
He seems to need someone
to have dinner with.

640
00:51:34,199 --> 00:51:36,360
Should I ask him
if he wants to eat with me?

641
00:51:37,070 --> 00:51:40,739
But if it's just the two of us,
he'll feel uncomfortable.

642
00:51:41,000 --> 00:51:43,769
As I'm his boss,
he won't be able to say no.

643
00:51:44,510 --> 00:51:46,639
Should I turn on the green light?

644
00:51:47,179 --> 00:51:50,050
It means I'm ready to go along
with him as long as he wants.

645
00:51:50,949 --> 00:51:53,679
But Mr. Um said
the signal light thing is childish.

646
00:51:53,719 --> 00:51:55,050
He has a point.

647
00:51:55,280 --> 00:51:58,989
It's embarrassing for a grown-up
to put colorful stickers on himself.

648
00:51:59,019 --> 00:52:00,090
(Embarrassed)

649
00:52:00,159 --> 00:52:03,860
But sometimes,
childish gestures break the ice.

650
00:52:04,230 --> 00:52:07,130
Ms. Chae made these for me.
I should pluck up the courage.

651
00:52:22,480 --> 00:52:25,349
Mr. Um?

652
00:52:27,019 --> 00:52:28,250
Mr. Um.

653
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:31,719
Mr. Um.

654
00:52:34,460 --> 00:52:36,460
How can he never buy me any meal?

655
00:52:38,590 --> 00:52:41,800
We had a shared destiny once.

656
00:52:43,000 --> 00:52:44,199
Everything's pointless.

657
00:52:46,539 --> 00:52:47,699
Gosh, it's hot.

658
00:52:49,800 --> 00:52:50,909
What a waste.

659
00:52:57,949 --> 00:53:00,019
VR movies surpass the boundary...

660
00:53:00,449 --> 00:53:03,219
between imagination and the reality
and the limits of space.

661
00:53:04,119 --> 00:53:07,659
VR movies will set a new paradigm...

662
00:53:07,719 --> 00:53:09,559
in the 120-year-long history
of movies.

663
00:53:09,590 --> 00:53:10,730
Oh, my.

664
00:53:10,929 --> 00:53:13,800
We're taking the innovative step
into the new world...

665
00:53:14,000 --> 00:53:16,869
before anyone else in the country.

666
00:53:17,329 --> 00:53:20,070
I'm co-CEO of Brain, Kang Woo Il.
Thank you.

667
00:53:27,139 --> 00:53:28,239
Oh, my.

668
00:53:33,579 --> 00:53:34,880
I knew it.

669
00:53:35,820 --> 00:53:38,250
We won't be the first ones anymore.

670
00:53:39,019 --> 00:53:41,920
You said it was lame
to strive for superlatives.

671
00:53:44,059 --> 00:53:47,000
The upper management needs to
make quick decisions...

672
00:53:47,030 --> 00:53:48,559
for things to move forward.

673
00:53:48,599 --> 00:53:52,369
We're spending forever
to just wait for the approval.

674
00:53:52,400 --> 00:53:55,699
The power struggle between the son
and the son-in-law. Round one.

675
00:53:56,099 --> 00:53:58,139
- Mr. Kang won.
- Yes.

676
00:53:58,309 --> 00:54:00,639
Ro Woon, your idea was great.

677
00:54:00,840 --> 00:54:02,809
You worked so hard.
You must be disappointed.

678
00:54:04,809 --> 00:54:05,949
Thank you.

679
00:54:09,320 --> 00:54:10,389
Thank you.

680
00:54:11,489 --> 00:54:14,789
I'm sure Boss has an idea.

681
00:54:15,289 --> 00:54:17,289
I'm sure he has another plan.

682
00:54:18,489 --> 00:54:20,659
You have no idea?

683
00:54:21,130 --> 00:54:23,130
You've been thinking all this time.

684
00:54:24,329 --> 00:54:28,000
I thought you turned on the red
light because you were thinking.

685
00:54:28,969 --> 00:54:31,340
Let's think together from now on.

686
00:54:55,929 --> 00:54:58,530
It's creepy here.
I'm scared ghosts will appear.

687
00:54:58,570 --> 00:55:00,840
It's very old-fashioned.

688
00:55:00,869 --> 00:55:02,769
It smells funny.

689
00:55:09,340 --> 00:55:12,980
My bottom and back will
start to ache.

690
00:55:13,010 --> 00:55:16,320
The seats are too close
to each other.

691
00:55:16,719 --> 00:55:17,889
I like it.

692
00:55:18,949 --> 00:55:21,389
I can sit close to my baby.

693
00:55:25,590 --> 00:55:27,760
This way. It's here.

694
00:55:27,800 --> 00:55:30,070
Since when are they so close?

695
00:55:30,730 --> 00:55:32,900
The rich boy is playing around,

696
00:55:33,400 --> 00:55:35,840
and an innocent girl fell for it.

697
00:55:45,050 --> 00:55:46,349
What happened?

698
00:55:46,550 --> 00:55:49,320
Are you two really dating?

699
00:55:50,219 --> 00:55:51,949
The thing is...

700
00:55:53,889 --> 00:55:56,019
He wants us to pretend
to be together.

701
00:55:56,059 --> 00:55:57,559
Sorry?

702
00:55:58,460 --> 00:56:01,329
He wants you to feel jealous.

703
00:56:01,860 --> 00:56:04,730
He wants to show you
how he can make a girl happy...

704
00:56:04,969 --> 00:56:08,869
and how nice he can be to a girl.

705
00:56:12,869 --> 00:56:17,280
Why don't you tell him how you feel?

706
00:56:19,510 --> 00:56:21,250
Not everyone can be...

707
00:56:21,980 --> 00:56:24,650
honest about their feelings
like you are.

708
00:56:26,420 --> 00:56:27,960
Everyone says...

709
00:56:28,360 --> 00:56:31,289
you should be confident so easily.

710
00:56:32,530 --> 00:56:35,699
But that's only possible
when you have someone listening.

711
00:56:37,369 --> 00:56:38,500
I have no one...

712
00:56:40,030 --> 00:56:42,269
willing to listen to me.

713
00:56:43,510 --> 00:56:45,769
Why do you say that?

714
00:56:45,869 --> 00:56:47,639
Can't you just pretend not to know?

715
00:56:48,780 --> 00:56:51,780
Se Jong is trying to make me happy.

716
00:56:53,079 --> 00:56:55,150
Who else would be...

717
00:56:55,349 --> 00:56:57,619
so nice to me?

718
00:57:02,619 --> 00:57:03,889
Gyo Ri.

719
00:57:09,559 --> 00:57:12,500
Without a theme
as unique as VR movies,

720
00:57:13,030 --> 00:57:14,469
it'd be hard to attract customers.

721
00:57:15,199 --> 00:57:18,139
Exactly. What a shame we missed it.

722
00:57:18,469 --> 00:57:20,809
It would have attracted attention
as it's a new thing.

723
00:57:23,780 --> 00:57:26,880
Among the cheesy superlatives,

724
00:57:26,920 --> 00:57:29,250
we've lost the best, the first,
and the biggest.

725
00:57:30,489 --> 00:57:34,789
But there's one perfect word left.

726
00:57:35,559 --> 00:57:36,619
What is it?

727
00:57:37,760 --> 00:57:38,860
The worst.

728
00:57:41,030 --> 00:57:43,400
- What's wrong with you?
- My gosh.

729
00:57:44,429 --> 00:57:47,769
It's not the biggest in Korea, and
the service isn't the best either,

730
00:57:47,800 --> 00:57:51,139
so let's come up with something
buzzworthy to make it memorable.

731
00:57:51,239 --> 00:57:53,940
There's no need to waste money
on renovations.

732
00:57:58,610 --> 00:58:00,349
How about a horror movie theater?

733
00:58:00,820 --> 00:58:03,050
"Visit the worst movie theater..."

734
00:58:03,750 --> 00:58:07,719
"for an unforgettable night of
horror that gives you the chills."

735
00:58:07,760 --> 00:58:10,260
- Horror movies?
- "Coming soon." Ta-da.

736
00:58:10,289 --> 00:58:11,289
That sounds good.

737
00:58:13,130 --> 00:58:15,059
- Pardon?
- Sorry?

738
00:58:16,929 --> 00:58:18,099
I like that idea.

739
00:58:19,469 --> 00:58:22,369
Let's go with Sun Bong's idea.

740
00:58:22,639 --> 00:58:24,869
What idea?
You mean what I just said?

741
00:58:25,809 --> 00:58:29,239
Gosh, I wasn't serious about it.
I was just being sarcastic.

742
00:58:30,579 --> 00:58:34,780
It's a great idea that twists
conventional strategies.

743
00:58:35,550 --> 00:58:38,750
- Goodness, I was just joking.
- He just said it to make us laugh.

744
00:58:39,150 --> 00:58:40,420
We can't use that idea.

745
00:58:40,559 --> 00:58:42,659
To make us laugh...
Yes, it was funny.

746
00:58:42,719 --> 00:58:46,860
Mr. Um, you have great wits
and an outstanding sense of humor.

747
00:58:47,360 --> 00:58:48,760
Me? I do?

748
00:58:49,900 --> 00:58:52,000
Gosh, what was that about?
Does that mean...

749
00:58:52,099 --> 00:58:54,469
he's taking what Sun Bong said
seriously?

750
00:58:54,800 --> 00:58:55,800
My gosh.

751
00:58:56,400 --> 00:58:57,639
I'm flustered.

752
00:58:58,239 --> 00:59:00,139
Sun Bong, tell us again.
What did you say?

753
00:59:00,679 --> 00:59:03,949
The green light is finally on.

754
00:59:25,900 --> 00:59:29,039
I've come up with an idea
for the promotional slogan.

755
00:59:29,869 --> 00:59:31,369
I thought that women...

756
00:59:32,010 --> 00:59:35,309
would hate to have dates at a place
known as the worst theater.

757
00:59:36,409 --> 00:59:40,110
How about we say the chairs will
help them test their boyfriends'...

758
00:59:40,150 --> 00:59:41,349
back strength?

759
00:59:41,949 --> 00:59:43,619
I see. Right.

760
00:59:43,849 --> 00:59:46,960
We do need to appeal
to female consumers.

761
00:59:47,159 --> 00:59:48,320
I like the idea.

762
00:59:48,389 --> 00:59:52,590
Great. There's this one too.

763
00:59:53,130 --> 00:59:54,929
You know those man-spreaders, right?

764
00:59:55,000 --> 00:59:59,670
The chairs will teach them manners
by making them close their legs.

765
01:00:01,139 --> 01:00:02,340
He smiled.

766
01:00:05,940 --> 01:00:07,239
There's another one.

767
01:00:08,940 --> 01:00:11,150
- There's another version.
- Is there?

768
01:00:11,250 --> 01:00:13,679
As you know, we'll market it
as the worst theater...

769
01:00:16,219 --> 01:00:17,719
Everyone says...

770
01:00:18,889 --> 01:00:22,059
you should be confident so easily.

771
01:00:23,789 --> 01:00:27,000
But that's only possible
when you have someone listening.

772
01:00:35,300 --> 01:00:36,539
What has gotten into him?

773
01:00:51,449 --> 01:00:53,019
What is wrong with him?

774
01:00:53,119 --> 01:00:55,590
He hasn't even budged from his desk
for hours.

775
01:00:56,019 --> 01:00:57,289
He looks so cool now.

776
01:01:04,670 --> 01:01:05,730
You got this.

777
01:01:06,469 --> 01:01:10,469
Boss was a good listener.

778
01:01:12,070 --> 01:01:13,940
The worst movie theater
in the world.

779
01:01:15,340 --> 01:01:19,679
It'll be sure to disappoint you
more than you can ever imagine.

780
01:01:20,150 --> 01:01:22,150
You're welcome to kick
the seat in front of you.

781
01:01:22,480 --> 01:01:24,719
You can certainly leave
your phone on the whole time.

782
01:01:24,820 --> 01:01:26,949
You may drink and dance away
inside the theater.

783
01:01:27,019 --> 01:01:30,119
If an ugly monster
shows up on the screen,

784
01:01:30,219 --> 01:01:32,329
you can go ahead
and throw your popcorn at it.

785
01:01:33,090 --> 01:01:34,760
- That's hilarious.
- You're doing a good job!

786
01:01:34,800 --> 01:01:37,429
Ladies and gentlemen, until when...

787
01:01:38,070 --> 01:01:41,469
do we have to live according
to the society's rigid standards?

788
01:01:42,199 --> 01:01:44,369
Forget the biggest, the best,
and the first.

789
01:01:44,510 --> 01:01:46,840
The worst day ever
can also be enjoyable.

790
01:01:46,869 --> 01:01:48,110
- That's right.
- Good!

791
01:01:48,480 --> 01:01:51,349
William Shakespeare said this.

792
01:01:52,010 --> 01:01:55,880
"The worst is not so long as
we can say this is the worst."

793
01:01:55,980 --> 01:01:57,550
The truly worst moment...

794
01:01:57,619 --> 01:02:01,360
is when we don't even have
strength to say so.

795
01:02:02,059 --> 01:02:04,690
We still have the energy to overcome
what we think is the worst.

796
01:02:04,829 --> 01:02:07,900
You, you, and you!

797
01:02:08,360 --> 01:02:12,300
Please get the most out
of the worst experience.

798
01:02:13,670 --> 01:02:16,469
The worst horror movie theater
in the entire world.

799
01:02:16,840 --> 01:02:19,969
The real horror starts now!

800
01:02:20,780 --> 01:02:21,809
You did it!

801
01:02:22,210 --> 01:02:23,510
- Amazing!
- That was awesome!

802
01:02:23,539 --> 01:02:25,550
- You did it.
- You did such a good job.

803
01:02:25,579 --> 01:02:28,150
The reason why
he has always been so quiet...

804
01:02:28,480 --> 01:02:29,780
- Don't cry!
- Don't cry!

805
01:02:31,989 --> 01:02:33,989
It wasn't because
he didn't want to talk.

806
01:02:34,590 --> 01:02:36,889
He probably wanted to listen.

807
01:02:59,280 --> 01:03:00,349
What was that about?

808
01:03:00,780 --> 01:03:03,019
- Just a high five.
- High five?

809
01:03:03,889 --> 01:03:05,320
- On my back?
- Give me five, then.

810
01:03:06,250 --> 01:03:08,420
See?
This is why I did it on your back.

811
01:03:12,559 --> 01:03:14,000
Help me organize this.

812
01:03:38,489 --> 01:03:40,019
In 1, 2, and 3.

813
01:03:51,769 --> 01:03:52,869
Look at the camera.

814
01:04:07,579 --> 01:04:08,619
My goodness.

815
01:04:08,820 --> 01:04:11,349
I hope you're not here
to steal our idea again.

816
01:04:13,690 --> 01:04:16,320
- What are you talking about?
- The VR cinema.

817
01:04:16,860 --> 01:04:18,590
We came up with that idea
a long time ago,

818
01:04:19,159 --> 01:04:21,699
but Boss took his sweet time
and ended up not approving it!

819
01:04:22,199 --> 01:04:25,030
There isn't much content
for VR cinemas yet,

820
01:04:25,170 --> 01:04:27,599
so a single-screen theater like this
won't be able to maintain business.

821
01:04:28,369 --> 01:04:30,300
Hwan Gi made the right decision.

822
01:04:30,400 --> 01:04:34,010
Work probably isn't his priority now
because of Ro Woon.

823
01:04:35,480 --> 01:04:38,380
- What did you just say?
- He's turned into a romantic.

824
01:04:39,050 --> 01:04:41,079
I guess you didn't know
he's been flirting with Ro Woon.

825
01:04:51,789 --> 01:04:53,329
Do you have anything to say to me?

826
01:04:54,159 --> 01:04:55,429
Just finish it up quickly.

827
01:04:59,099 --> 01:05:01,239
"My gosh, you're really good."

828
01:05:01,969 --> 01:05:03,840
"Where did you learn
how to do this?"

829
01:05:03,869 --> 01:05:06,610
"Thanks for helping us
reduce the expenses."

830
01:05:07,239 --> 01:05:11,110
Just for your information, those are
what others said to me.

831
01:05:12,280 --> 01:05:14,280
Don't put too much blood on me.

832
01:05:14,380 --> 01:05:16,579
I don't want to scare people.

833
01:05:17,989 --> 01:05:22,420
Your black hoodie is already
scaring everyone enough.

834
01:05:23,820 --> 01:05:25,860
I want to see myself in the mirror.
You're making me anxious.

835
01:05:26,230 --> 01:05:28,059
- Hand me a mirror.
- Please close your eyes.

836
01:05:28,460 --> 01:05:29,730
I need to do the eye makeup now.

837
01:05:31,699 --> 01:05:32,730
Goodness.

838
01:05:33,769 --> 01:05:34,800
I'll use this color.

839
01:05:48,050 --> 01:05:49,119
Oh, gosh...

840
01:05:49,420 --> 01:05:53,320
Please close your eyes. I need
to put this over your eyelids.

841
01:06:03,230 --> 01:06:05,869
What's up with you? I can't believe
you took that off yourself.

842
01:06:32,659 --> 01:06:33,829
What is with you?

843
01:06:35,000 --> 01:06:36,960
You're not avoiding eye contact.

844
01:06:37,869 --> 01:06:39,099
I am avoiding it.

845
01:06:42,400 --> 01:06:43,400
Are you...

846
01:06:45,469 --> 01:06:47,269
not going to close your eyes?

847
01:06:48,039 --> 01:06:49,440
I'm doing my very best...

848
01:06:50,380 --> 01:06:52,010
to avoid it.

849
01:07:05,760 --> 01:07:06,960
Is this...

850
01:07:08,530 --> 01:07:11,800
a staring match or what?

851
01:07:13,769 --> 01:07:15,639
Are we doing this because...

852
01:07:16,599 --> 01:07:20,110
turning away or closing eyes first
means losing?

853
01:07:22,940 --> 01:07:24,480
Close your eyes, please.

854
01:07:26,179 --> 01:07:28,550
What will you do
if I poke your eyes?

855
01:08:55,470 --> 01:08:58,170
(My Shy Boss)

856
01:08:58,310 --> 01:09:00,270
- Boss.
- Don't stay by my side.

857
01:09:00,310 --> 01:09:01,609
You thanked me...

858
01:09:01,640 --> 01:09:03,279
- for being by your side.
- Just a second!

859
01:09:03,340 --> 01:09:04,750
Did I do something wrong?

860
01:09:04,779 --> 01:09:07,380
- One of my employees bothers me.
- One, two.

861
01:09:07,409 --> 01:09:09,020
- One, two.
- Bring it back.

862
01:09:09,180 --> 01:09:11,090
- Run, run.
- It's not Chae Ro Woon.

863
01:09:11,119 --> 01:09:13,420
- She's gone.
- Boss?

864
01:09:13,689 --> 01:09:15,060
Ms. Chae.

865
01:09:15,090 --> 01:09:17,529
- Either bring her back,
- The red light?

866
01:09:17,560 --> 01:09:19,659
- Ms. Chae?
- or don't show it.

867
01:09:19,689 --> 01:09:22,130
- Yi Soo needs you now.
- What are you doing now?

868
01:09:22,159 --> 01:09:24,729
- Get lost.
- Excuse me.

869
01:09:24,770 --> 01:09:27,170
Will you really be able
to do the presentation?

870
01:09:27,199 --> 01:09:28,800
- I will.
- Not the presentation.

871
01:09:28,840 --> 01:09:30,369
- You won't be able to do it.
- What if I do it?

872
01:09:30,569 --> 01:09:31,939
I want Ro Woon back.
